@startuml
title Sales Management - Sequence Diagram (Create & Approve TopUpRequest)

actor Customer
actor Admin
participant "TopUpRequestCreateView" as CreateView
participant "TopUpRequestListView" as ListView
participant "TopUpRequestApproveView" as ApproveView
database "Customer" as CustomerModel
database "TopUpRequest" as TopUpModel
database "Wallet" as WalletModel

== Customer creates request ==
Customer -> CreateView: GET /wallet/topup/create/
alt Not authenticated
  CreateView --> Customer: Redirect /login/
else Staff user
  CreateView --> Customer: Redirect / (home)
else Valid customer user
  CreateView --> Customer: Render form
end

Customer -> CreateView: POST amount, note
CreateView -> CreateView: Validate amount format and value > 0
alt Invalid amount
  CreateView --> Customer: Render form + error message
else Valid amount
  CreateView -> CustomerModel: get request.user.customer_profile
  alt Customer not found
    CreateView --> Customer: Redirect / + error message
  else Found
    CreateView -> TopUpModel: create(status=PENDING, amount, note)
    TopUpModel --> CreateView: TopUpRequest created
    CreateView --> Customer: Redirect /wallet/ + success message
  end
end

== Admin approves request ==
Admin -> ListView: GET /wallet/topup/requests/
ListView -> TopUpModel: all().order_by('-id')
TopUpModel --> ListView: request list
ListView --> Admin: Render list

Admin -> ApproveView: POST /wallet/topup/requests/{id}/approve/
ApproveView -> TopUpModel: get_object_or_404(id)
TopUpModel --> ApproveView: topup_request

alt topup_request.status != PENDING
  ApproveView --> Admin: Redirect list + error message
else status == PENDING
  ApproveView -> WalletModel: get wallet by topup_request.customer
  WalletModel --> ApproveView: wallet
  ApproveView -> WalletModel: balance += amount; save()
  ApproveView -> TopUpModel: status=APPROVED; save()
  ApproveView --> Admin: Redirect list + success message
end

@enduml
